                    <ab></ab>
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName ref="#people/7"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Otto</persName> divina favente clemencia Romanorum
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Notum sit universis
                        nostris fidelibus, quia pro divino amore et pro <persName key="#Bishops"
                            ref="#people/171">Leonis</persName> nostri <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcopi</rs> petitione, audita dilapidatione <orgName
                            key="#Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/81">sancti
                            Eusebii</orgName> ab uxoratis antecessoribus facta, concessimus sancte
                            <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/106">Vercellensi</placeName>
                        ecclesie ut in <rs key="#Castle">castello</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/237"
                            key="#Public_exactions #Fodrum #Profits_of_justice #Teloneum #Privileges #Districtio"
                            >sancte Agathe</placeName> aut in <rs key="#Burgi">burgo</rs> eius aut
                        per quinque miliaria in circuitu nullus unquam hominum placitum teneat aut
                            <rs key="#Fodrum">fodrum</rs> colligat aut <rs key="#Albergaria/gifori"
                            >albergarias</rs> faciat publicas aut ullam <rs key="#Public_exactions"
                            >publicam exactionem</rs> exigat, nisi Vercellensis episcopus aut eius
                            <rs key="#Missus">missus</rs>, in tota campagnia nullus <rs
                            key="#Teloneum">thelonia</rs> capiat, nullus <rs key="#Markets"
                            >mercata</rs> habeat publica, nisi Vercellensis ecclesia. Dedimus
                        Vercellensi ecclesie <placeName ref="#places/210"
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Andurnum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/827">Mulinariam</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/208"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Ponderanam</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/211"
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >montem Cisidola</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/206"
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Galianicum</placeName> cum omnibus suis pertinentiis; dedimus sancto
                        Eusebio omnia predia maledicti <persName key="#Emperor/king #Marquis/duke"
                            ref="#people/172">Ardoini</persName> filii <persName ref="#people/291"
                            key="#parentOf">Dadonis</persName>, quia eius episcopum interfecit et
                        incendit, <placeName ref="#places/3728"
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rouoredum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/332">Riuarolum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/829">Riuaruptam</placeName>; redidimus <geogName
                            ref="#estates/129"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/590">Canauam</placeName></geogName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rordiliteguam</placeName>; dedimus <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/830">Sparono</placeName> castellum, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >vallem Suanam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/566">vallem Origanam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/331">Fontanedum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/831">Barsan</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/832">Suanam</placeName> et omnia predia Ardoini ubicunque
                        iacent, cum omnibus pertinentiis; dedimus sancto Eusebio <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >cortem</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/164">Sisbalanam</geogName> et <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/220">Gatinaram</placeName> in integrum, que iuste perdidit
                            <persName ref="#people/202" key="#Marquis/duke">Ardicinus</persName>
                        filius Ardoini marchionis, quia vocatus ad <rs key="#Palatium">palacium</rs>
                        Papiense ut legem faceret, noctu aufugit et imperatoris presenciam nullius
                        reverencie habuit; confirmamus et redimus sancto Eusebio omne <rs
                            key="#Forests">forestum</rs> de Loceio et totam <placeName
                            ref="#places/96"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >scilvam Rouaxindam</placeName>; confirmamus sancto Eusebio <orgName
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/107">monasterium de <placeName
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                                ref="#places/328">Lauceio</placeName></orgName> cum omnibus suis
                        pertinentiis et confirmamus omnia <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma"
                            >precepta</rs> eidem sancte ecclesie a nostris predecessoribus facta.
                        Statuimus quoque, ut omnes filii vel filie <rs key="#Coloni/tenants"
                            >colonorum</rs> ex familia sancti Eusebii in servitute ecclesie maneant
                        neque libertas matris, si colono servo adhesit, hiis qui nati fuerint,
                        prosit volumus. Rogamus eciam successores nostros et sub dei timore
                        contestamur, ut omnia <rs key="#Commutatio">cambia</rs> illicita et <rs
                            key="#Slave">servos</rs> ecclesie illicite liberatos ad pristinum usum
                        venire cogant et ad antiquam servitutem venire compellant, maxime <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/201">Ingonis</persName> episcopi omnia
                        cambia frangant, qui pro adulterio sanctam Agatham cum servis et ancillis et
                        ipsas mortuorum sepulturas ab ecclesia alienavit, <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/123">monasterium sancti Stephani</orgName>
                        anullavit, quia Cabaliacam per cambium diabolicum ei abstulit, Lauceium
                        monasterium disperdidit, quia Alite ab eo alienavit, ipsam civitatem
                        Vercellensem ita populavit quod nec terras neque servos ibi esse permisit.
                        Omnia que superius dicta sunt et <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/329">Caualiacam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/48">Alicem</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/237">sanctam Agatham </placeName>et omnia eorum pertinencia
                        sancta Vercellensis ecclesia habeat teneat et imperpetuum proprietatem
                        diiudicet. Si quis vero ullam molestiam de hiis omnibus ipsis episcopis
                        ecclesie Vercellensis fecerit, <rs key="#Penalty">mille libras iusti
                            auri</rs> componat Vercellensi ecclesie, medietatem ei et nobis alteram,
                        et hoc preceptum in sua maneat firmitate. Quod ut credatur et conservetur,
                        manu nostra hoc firmavimus et nostro sigillo precepimus insigniri. Signum
                        domini Ottonis (M.) invictissimi augusti. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
